The invention may be understood by reference to the following description taken in conjunction with the accompanying drawings, in which like reference numerals identify like elements, and in which:


FIG. 1 is a stylized block diagram of a prior art R2R digital-to-analog converter;


FIG. 2 illustrates a digital-to-analog converter in accordance with the present invention;


FIG. 3 depicts one embodiment of a strobe shift register that can be employed by the digital-to-analog converter of FIG. 2;


FIG. 4 illustrates a timing diagram of the strobe shift register of FIG. 3;


FIG. 5 depicts one embodiment of a clock generator that can be employed by the strobe shift register of FIG. 3.


FIG. 6 illustrates a schematic diagram of an alternative embodiment of a strobe shift register that can be employed by the digital-to-analog converter of FIG. 2; and


FIG. 7 illustrates a schematic diagram of one embodiment of a clock generator that can be employed by the strobe shift register of FIG. 6.
